                    "description": "Graduation project on the life-cycle assessment of a system in which a photovoltaic panel combined with a battery would power a ventilation system. This system, which is stand-alone, meaning that the PV module is not connected to the electricity grid, is compared to a situation in which the same ventilation system is powered by electricity taken directly from the national grid. In addition, a third scenario was created, in which the PV module is connected to the grid, making it possible for it to send the electricity not used to power the ventilation system on the grid, therefore reducing CO2 emissions.\n\nFor this project, the LCA software OpenLCA and the EcoInvent 3.6 database were used.",
